text: The South Central Ambulance Service NHS Foundation Trust runs the ambulance service for the counties of Berkshire, Buckinghamshire, Oxfordshire and most of Hampshire. It also runs a patient transport service, first aid training fornthe public, a community equipment service and logistic services. In June 2011, it was said to be England's top performing ambulance service, but it was rated Inadequate by the Care Quality Commission in 2022. == References == Category:NHS ambulance services trusts
title: South Central Ambulance Service
